                            <comment id="264041" author="ofaaland" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2020 18:44:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If crash+bug resulted in the situation described, would current lfsck detect and report the issue, even if it cannot yet repair it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="134832" author="adilger" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2015 09:08:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This would essentially allow migrating to or from a striped directory, or changing the directory striping arbitrarily, so long as it was clear what the &quot;goal&quot; directory count was, and the directory was marked with &lt;tt&gt;LMV_HASH_FLAG_MIGRATION&lt;/tt&gt; so that clients knew to query all of the directory shards when doing a lookup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
